          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "To the concern person,\nDear sir/ma'am,\nI meant to give a 5 star to the school but there are few areas to be rectified and you have to pay attention to as soon as possible.\n\nSpoken English is not upto the mark in the younger classes of the primary section where formative yrs are really important... Children have got a typical accent of the southern region... Some words are mispronounced... Spoken English, Hindi or Tamil is very important in the formative yrs of a growing child otherwise they have a bad accent learnt by the teachers.... Kids really look up to their teachers hence they only follow what they say......\nSecondly chennai is too hot a place for kids having to do PT or yoga in the afternoon... PT should be over before 9.00am followed by assembly n prayer. Chennai is a hot place n the sun is really sharp... All of us want to sit inside during the day, then you should not expect kids to do PT at that time of the day. They come inside sweating n are pretty tired for the next period.\nYou should also be aware that most of the kids in the younger classes were 2yrs n eyes when the pandemic happened.... Most of them had COVID... They have a weak respiratory system hence their immunity is not upto the mark.... Also remember that none of these kids were vaccinated against COVID hence they are susceptible to getting ill very frequently.....\nPls keep all this in mind n bring abt changes wherever needed.\nThanking you,\nYours sincerely,\nSangeeta Harinarain",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
